cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the decidability of a logic (MITL) in the context of reactive synthesis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as reactive synthesis is a problem in AI, and the paper proposes an algorithm to solve a specific subcase of the problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the synthesis of controllers, which can be seen as a programming task. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the synthesis of controllers for temporal specifications, which can be seen as a language recognition problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the synthesis of controllers for real-time systems.
